burlap.behavior.singleagent

Interface MDPSolverInterface

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ModelLearningPlanner, Planner
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActorCritic, ApproximateQLearning, ARTDP, AStar, BeliefSparseSampling, BestFirst, BFS, BoundedRTDP, DeterministicPlanner, DFS, DifferentiableDP, DifferentiableSparseSampling, DifferentiableVI, DynamicProgramming, DynamicWeightedAStar, FittedVI, GradientDescentQLearning, GradientDescentSarsaLam, IDAStar, LimitedMemoryDFS, LSPI, MDPSolver, PolicyEvaluation, PolicyIteration, PotentialShapedRMax, PrioritizedSweeping, QLearning, QMDP, RTDP, SarsaLam, SparseSampling, StaticWeightedAStar, TDLambda, TimeIndexedTDLambda, UCT, ValueIteration, VIModelLearningPlanner, WeightedGreedy

    public interface MDPSolverInterface
    The top-level interface for algorithms that solve MDPs. In general, classes should probably subclass the MDPSolver abstract class instead of using this interface directly, since the MDPSolver will provide relevant data members, implement these methods, and provide additional helper methods.
    Author:
    James MacGlashan.

    • Method Detail

      • solverInit

        void solverInit(SADomain domain,
                double gamma,
                HashableStateFactory hashingFactory)
        Initializes the solver with the common elements.
        Parameters:
        domain - the domain to be solved.
        gamma - the MDP discount factor
        hashingFactory - the hashing factory used to store states (may be set to null if the solver is not tabular)

      • resetSolver

        void resetSolver()
        This method resets all solver results so that a solver can be restarted fresh as if had never solved the MDP.

      • setDomain

        void setDomain(SADomain domain)
        Sets the domain of this solver. NOTE: this will also reset the actions this solver uses to the actions of the provided domain. If you have previously added non-domain referenced actions through the addActionType(ActionType) method, you will have to do so again.
        Parameters:
        domain - the domain this solver should use.

      • setModel

      • getActionTypes

        List<ActionType> getActionTypes()
        Returns a copy of all actions this solver uses for reasoning; including added actions that are not part of the domain specification (e.g., Options). Modifying the returned list will not modify the action list this solver uses.
        Returns:
        a List of all actions this solver uses.
